  "texts": [
    "( 4) Medoid (MD): This strategy fixes the medoid node as entry point during query answering and uses its neighbors as seeds.",
    "(5) Single Fixed Random Entry Point (SF): A random node is selected and fixed as the entry point for all searches.",
    "This node and the nodes connected to it are used as seeds.",
    "( 6) K-Sampled Random Seeds (KS): For each query, 𝑘 random nodes are selected to warm up the set of candidate answers.",
    "This approach is supported in DPG [86], NSG [54], and Vamana [129] which choose the medoid as the entry point and enhance the list of initial seeds with the random nodes."
  ],
